06/12/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Senior representatives of the Social Democratic Party (SDP) and the Alliance of Independent Social Democrats (SNSD) have agreed that a new central level government should be established as soon as possible, and said they are committed to BiH's European future. 
SDP leader Zlatko Lagumdzija and his SNSD counterpart, Republika Srpska President Milorad Dodik, met on Saturday (December 4th) in Sarajevo to discuss possible co-operation. 
They voiced readiness to tackle thorny issues including constitutional reform, distributing state and military property and conducting a population census. 
Representatives of the two parties will meet again within a week. 
(Fena, Nezavisne Novine - 04/12/10)
